He was afraid of the dark, and he had to keep the lights on all night long. David was afraid that he would see a monster in the dark. Anna was a good wife, and she tried to help him. She thought of all possible solutions to solve David's problem. You know what she finally came up with? They decided to stay active during the night and make themselves very busy and tired. When the sun rose, both of them became very exhausted and fell asleep very quickly. They then lived happily together and called themselves Big Owl and Small Owl.
